            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-amber-300">Premium only</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-emerald-300">Full</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-emerald-300">Via chat</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2">Grammar teaching</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-amber-300">Implicit</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-emerald-300">Explicit</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-emerald-300">From tutor</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2">Human interaction</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-rose-300">No</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-rose-300">No</td>
            <td class="border border-slate-700 px-4 py-2 text-emerald-300">Yes</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Our Verdict</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Pimsleur is a well-designed, science-backed language learning program. Its audio-only approach is unique and effective for building speaking skills and pronunciation. If you have a long commute or want to practice English while doing other activities, Pimsleur is an excellent choice.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      However, Pimsleur is not a complete English learning solution. You'll need to supplement it with reading, writing, and grammar practice from other sources. At $23.95/month, it's also more expensive than many competitors. But for what it does, building spoken English skills efficiently, it does very well.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      We recommend Pimsleur as a <strong>supplement</strong> to your main learning method, not as your only tool. Use it alongside apps like <a href="/reviews/duolingo/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">Duolingo</a> or <a href="/reviews/babbel/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">Babbel</a> for vocabulary and grammar, then book real speaking practice with a tutor for the part Pimsleur cannot give you.
    </p>

